You said  in the chat, and friend, after seeing that phrasing, I was admittedly very nervous about opening this response you penned. (especially since another individual had basically previously commented about how one of my concerns about the piece was legitimate/expressed dislike)

(anyways. Digressing already. Woke up after midnight from sleep paralysis, don't mind me)

I was trying to achieve a couple of things with this piece.

1. I didn't know how to articulate it at first, but a Reddit user helped. I wanted a 'Pet the Dog' /'morality pet' situation for the Foundation. they justFoundation folk have a thankless job, like I mentioned earlier in the thread. My little Dierdre needed a better life. Even the Foundation would be preferable to what she had. She can have a normal childhood, now. 🌈

2. I wanted a happy ending for at least one child stuck inside these nightmare situations. Her house was a broken home, so she burned it down. She doesn't need to make fires anymore, either. She's risen from the ashes and soared off into the new dawn. Even if it's from behind the bars of a cage.

